Lawyer Belghoul Saadi, 42, has been killed after  being kidnapped in continued unrest in Algeria, the daily newspaper L'Opinion  reported Tuesday.
It said that Saadi, kidnapped Friday, was found with his throat cut on  Saturday. Saadi was taken from his home in Haouch el-Mokhfi, in an Islamic  fundamentalist sector east of Algiers and known as the "triangle of fear".
The daily did not say who carried out the killing but noted that Saadi was  a defender of Islamic fundamentalists in Algerian courts. He was the fourth  lawyer to be killed in recent months.
